{
  "text": "To determine the cross-correlations, we first go to the frame of reference where the rotational-rotational part of the mobility matrix is diagonal, and evaluate the correlation matrix C diag in this frame, using the explicit expressions from [CITATION_1] . Then, with the use of the 3 \u00d7 3 transformation matrix T , we transform it to the original frame of reference,",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "29907941"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "29907941": {
      "title": "Note: Brownian motion of colloidal particles of arbitrary shape",
      "abstract": "The analytical expressions for the time-dependent cross correlations of the translational and rotational Brownian displacements of a particle with arbitrary shape are derived. The reference center is arbitrary, and the reference frame is such that the rotational-rotational diffusion tensor is diagonal."
    }
  }
}